President Donald J. Trump and President Xi Jinping of China had a phone conversation in which they discussed various topics. President Trump agreed, at the request of President Xi, to honor the "one China" policy. Representatives of both countries will engage in discussions and negotiations on mutual interests. The call was cordial, and both leaders extended best wishes to each other's countries. They also invited each other to meet in their respective countries and expressed their anticipation for further talks with successful outcomes.